# Code Standards and Best Practices

## Script Organization
The enhancer script [embed-enhancer.js](mdc:embed-enhancer.js) follows these principles:
- Clear function documentation with JSDoc comments
- Modular function design for maintainability
- Consistent error handling patterns
- Non-blocking operations where possible
- Defensive programming with fallbacks

## Configurator Standards
The configurator [configurator/index.html](mdc:configurator/index.html) follows these guidelines:
- Semantic HTML structure
- Bootstrap 5.2.3 components and utilities
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Clear user feedback for all actions
- Comprehensive form validation
- Accessible UI elements

## General Practices
- Use clear, descriptive variable names
- Add comments for complex logic
- Include error handling for API calls
- Maintain backward compatibility
- Follow progressive enhancement principles
- Keep dependencies minimal and current

## Testing Considerations
- Test across major browsers
- Verify mobile responsiveness
- Check all filter combinations
- Validate error handling
- Test with various CrowdWork configurations
- Verify performance with large event sets
